The principal exponents of this creed were, besides Pound, the late Huey Long, Father Charles E. Coughlin, Gerald L. K. Smith, and Lawrence Dennis. American fascism had its roots in American populism; it pursued the same ends and even used many of the same slogans.

"Great men, like great periods, are explosive materials in which an immense force is accumulated; it is always pre-requisite for such men, historically and physiologically, that for a long period there has been a collecting, a heaping up, an economizing, and a hoarding with respect to them, that for a long time no explosion has taken place." ‚Äî Nietzsche, Twilight of the Idols In the above, Nietzsche is suggesting that in order for great men to emerge, and for the higher-type to be born (or re-born), there needs to be a prolonged period of building, where "a hoarding" of energy, ideas, and resources is accumulated. This energy, reaching a point of critical mass, is then unleashed upon the world in a manner that catalyzes profound transformation. Julius Caesar was one such great man. Caesar's actions brought about the destruction of the decrepit and decadent Roman Republic, and in its place, through the dynamic explosion of transformative energy, the Roman Empire, the Imperium of Augustus and his successors, was born. From this, various questions are begged: When will the next release of "immense force" be unleashed? Who will be the next Caesar, Charlemagne, or Napoleon? And more aptly, is such a transformation still possible? I believe that transformation is possible, and it starts first with YOU, the individual. Become better and more than what you are.

url_title: Stockholm University Press
url_description:
Current scientific advances are reshaping our understanding of prehistory, offering unprecedented insights into the movements and kinship patterns of prehistoric populations. These new advances provide us with detailed information on several aspects of the early speakers of Indo-European and their lives. However, the prehistoric humans that we know through bones and potsherds were once real people speaking real languages and having specific beliefs, mythological tales and poetic expressions.

With this book, we want to apply a multidisciplinary approach that combines historical linguistics, archaeology, and comparative religion in order to improve our understanding of the early speakers of Indo-European. The book is a collection of papers by specialists in historical linguistics, archaeology and comparative religion, each examining different facets of the early Indo-European speakers, including their language, culture, and religious practices.

Pharmakos: Human Sacrifice in Ancient Greece The ancient Greek term "Pharmakos" (œÜŒ¨œÅŒºŒ±Œ∫ŒøœÇ) derives from "pharmakon" (œÜŒ¨œÅŒºŒ±Œ∫ŒøŒΩ), meaning a substance with the power to heal or, inversely, harm. In a ceremonial context, "Pharmakos" refers to a ritualistic human sacrifice or exile, where a person, often already condemned, was used as a vessel to cleanse the community of its impurities. This sacrificial rite was believed to purify the populace and appease the gods during times of crisis or catastrophe. During the Thargelia festival in early ancient Athens, which celebrated the birthdays of the divine twins, Apollo and Artemis, and marked the beginning of the grain harvest, the Pharmakos ritual took on a particularly dramatic and gruesome form. This festival, practiced from at least the 6th century BC to as late as the 5th century BC, involved a ritual described by Hipponax of Kolophon, an ancient Greek poet. He provides a vivid account: two of the ugliest people in the city, whose appearance was seen as a sign of divine disfavor and a blight to the community, were chosen for ritual sacrifice. Adorned with fig necklaces, these wretched souls were paraded through the streets and subjected to beatings by the populace with fig-wood sticks. This public spectacle of suffering, somewhat reminiscent of the "auto-da-f√©" of the much later Spanish Inquisition, aimed to transfer the community's impurities onto these individuals. Ultimately, their execution was believed to purify and sanctify the greater community. The ritual's crescendo was as gruesome as it was symbolic. The chosen men were led to the seashore, a liminal space believed to be a threshold between worlds, where they were stoned to death or summarily drowned by the community. Their bodies were then burned, and the ashes were either cast into the sea or scattered over the fields, symbolizing the dispersal of the community's miasma, a form of spiritual pollution. There is some debate about the accuracy of Hipponax‚Äôs account. Like many ancient sources who wrote about earlier events, the temporal distance between his writings and the actual performance of the ritual has led to varying interpretations. Despite these doubts, the essence of the Pharmakos ritual remains clear: it was a momentous act of communal expiation and Hellenic religious piety, deeply rooted in the belief that sacrificing a human life could invoke divine favor and bring about renewal.

A true traditional man does not indulge in cheap pleasures, but works hard to save his resources in order to secure a future for his offspring and wife. He has firm beliefs and does not care what others think of him. The father is an authoritative figure who maintains order and discipline in the home, ensuring that his children are raised to be strong members of society. Without order and discipline, we get chaos and degeneration. Our enemies constantly attack men in an attempt to feminize us. They want to take away masculinity from men and our natural paternal role of being disciplinarians for our families. We are told that masculinity is "toxic." They have turned the once brave alpha male leader into a weak coward who is submissive and afraid to stand up for himself. We must stop the feminization of men. Go to the gym, read books, improve yourself, be brave, and stand up against injustices that are done to you. Focus on building a strong family and extinguish the anti-male propaganda that our enemies impose on us.

The problems that accumulate penetrate deep into our society and break it down. To secure the future of our people, a radical upheaval - a revolution - is needed. Reformists are trying to convince us that we can slowly fix this broken system and bring it back to the way it was. We do not want a return to something that was not stable from the very beginning, nor is it possible to revive the dead. Dead bodies are usually buried, so this system should be buried as well. The national revolution requires a struggle not only on a broader level, in the sense of the state management system, but also a complete change in people's thinking and in their understanding of the world around them. üá¨üáß The belief of the Third Position is that the world's national revolution can only be achieved by shaping a new man, a militant who practices what he preaches. Such a new man must embody our ideal in such a way that he acts within himself as the highest form of propaganda for the Third Position in the community in which he lives and works. As each individual develops his or her spiritual qualities, Europe will move forward towards a new empire. The third position is a spiritually motivated view of the world that rejects the acquired wisdom of the modern world that all peoples and cultures are forever condemned to choose between the left and the right, communism and capitalism. Based on a good knowledge of human nature and its interests, the Third Position does not seek unsustainable centrism, but a way of thinking and acting that truly transcends the sterile hatred of the modern world. The third position is therefore the only opposition of the 21st century. Without a spiritual revolution ‚Äì a method of purification and refinement that is carried out by an individual throughout his life ‚Äì our people will in no way be different from the degenerates who caused the horrors of the modern world and who acted on a purely materialistic understanding of life and history. Since the family is the primary element and centre of every healthy society, it follows that its strength and unity are essential to the stability, happiness and development of the nation in all its aspects, both material and spiritual. For this reason, the Third Position opposes all agencies and policies that seek in any way to limit, undermine or destroy family life. The main damage that has been done in our time can be described as: Masonry, liberalism, nihilism, capitalism, communism, Marxism, imperialism, anarchy, modernism and the new age. Each of these ideas ‚Äì materialistic in essence ‚Äì is philosophically wrong and discredited in practice. So the Third Position unreservedly condemns them all and confirms that opposition to all forms of materialism is central to ideology.Third position. Third position believes that in a healthy social order there is a vital balance between rural and urban. In itself, Ruralism is far healthier, because it possesses all that is necessary for life, but this does not diminish the fact that complementary urbanism ‚Äì consisting of a village, a village, a market, centres of technological progress that does not pollute, a light industry and research institutes ‚Äì can add much to the benefits of human existence. This balance between rural and urbanism is considered central to the world view of the Third Position. Our idea is to oppose multi-racial and multi-cultural communities on European soil. It is only true that Europe belongs to the White Europeans because the White Europeans built a nation and they are this nation. In other words, this forced multiculturalism seeks to destroy the living ground on which all peoples have their roots, their identity, their beings. The third position rejects all attempts to impose this inhuman conformity on humanity. It is precisely because the Third Position seeks to build a new social order that it recognises that all the peoples and cultures of Europe, which adhere to the basic principles of the Third Position, must work closely together in an atmosphere of mutual trust and support.The third position is of a revolutionary nature, and [as] such an idea, it calls for a significant defiance of the influence of a world that is increasingly driven by political correctness and people who are losing their identity. Instead of wasting time on apologies or constant debate, we should continue to march forward and pave the way for revolutionary action. We must continue to fight in our devotion to the truth, reach out to the masses and defy the efforts that are trying to demoralize us and divert us from our goals. We should maximize our support for the things that really matter and hasten the demise of degenerate systems that have caused nothing but suffering and damage to our people. Linked text: CLICK

üá¨üáß Serbs are traditionally a warrior, frontiersman and freedom-loving nation, which they are justifiably proud of. Evidence for the Serbian warrior spirit, among other things, is that they belong to the rare nations in the world, where the departure of recruits to the army is celebrated noisily and joyfully as if it were a wedding or the birth of a child. The army played an important role in Serbian society. The act of going to military service was considered a path through which every young man goes, and at the end of it he becomes a man.No one who somehow escaped the army was considered a man, and deserters were looked upon with the greatest contempt. Throughout its modern history, militarism has shaped Serbia. There was not a generation that did not take a rifle to fight against the Turks by going to the forests, or against the Austrians by going to the front - always in a war of good will, understanding it as a duty. War was a call to which Serbs always responded, not because they like to die, but because of the militaristic society that has been created for centuries.

It is time to move to the right side of history and stop living in ignorance, the future of our children, our country and our people depends on it.

üá∑üá∏ –ï–∫–æ–ª–æ–≥–∏—ò–∞ —ò–µ —ò–µ–¥–∞–Ω –æ–¥ –æ—Å–Ω–æ–≤–Ω–∏—Ö —Ç–µ–º–µ—ô–∞ –Ω–∞—à–µ–≥ –ø—É—Ç–∞. –ú–∏—Å–∞–æ —ò–µ —É–≤–µ–∫ –±–∏–ª–∞ –∑–∞—Å–Ω–æ–≤–∞–Ω–∞ –Ω–∞ –ø—Ä–∏—Ä–æ–¥–Ω–∏–º –∑–∞–∫–æ–Ω–∏–º–∞. –î–∞–Ω–∞—à—ö–∏ –µ–∫–æ–ª–æ–∑–∏, –º–∞—Ö–æ–º –∞–Ω–∞—Ä—Ö–∏—Å—Ç–∏ –∏ –∫–æ–º—É–Ω–∏—Å—Ç–∏, –∫–∞–∂—É –¥–∞ —ò–µ –µ–∫–æ–ª–æ–≥–∏—ò–∞ —ö–∏—Ö–æ–≤ –ø—Ä–æ–Ω–∞–ª–∞–∑–∞–∫. –ê–ª–∏ —Ç–æ –Ω–∏—ò–µ —Å—Ç–∏–Ω–∞. –£ –ù–µ–º–∞—á–∫–æ–º —Ä–∞—ò—Ö—É —ò–µ –ø—Ä–æ–ø–∞–≥–∏—Ä–∞–Ω –ø—Ä–∏–Ω—Ü–∏–ø –∫—Ä–≤–∏ –∏ —Ç–ª–∞, –º–ª–∞–¥–∏—õ–∏ –∏–∑ –æ–º–ª–∞–¥–∏–Ω—Å–∫–∏—Ö –∑–∞–¥—Ä—É–≥–∞ —Å—É —Å—Ç–∞–ª–Ω–æ –±–æ—Ä–∞–≤–∏–ª–∏ —É –ø—Ä–∏—Ä–æ–¥–∏, —Å–∞–º —ö–∏—Ö–æ–≤ –≤–æ—í–∞ –∏–∞–∫–æ —ò–µ —ò–µ–æ —Ö—Ä–∞–Ω—É –∂–∏–≤–æ—Ç–∏—ö—Å–∫–æ–≥ –ø–æ—Ä–µ–∫–ª–∞ - –Ω–∞–≥–∏—ö–∞–æ –≤–µ—Ç–µ—Ä–∏—ò–∞–Ω—Å–∫–æ–º –Ω–∞—á–∏–Ω—É –∏—Å—Ö—Ä–∞–Ω–µ(—ò–∞—ò–∞,—Å–∏—Ä,–º–ª–µ–∫–æ –∏ –≤–æ—õ–µ/–ø–æ–≤—Ä—õ–µ), –≤–æ–ª–µ–æ –∂–∏–≤–æ—Ç–∏—ö–µ –∏ —á–µ—Å—Ç–æ –±–æ—Ä–∞–≤–∏–æ —É –ø–ª–∞–Ω–∏–Ω–∞–º–∞. –ù–µ–º–∞—á–∫–∞ —ò–µ –±–∏–ª–∞ –ø—Ä–≤–∞ –∑–µ–º—ô–∞ —Å–∞ –∑–∞–∫–æ–Ω–∏–º–∞ –Ω–∞ –∑–∞—à—Ç–∏—Ç—É –ø—Ä–∏—Ä–æ–¥–µ. –ê —à—Ç–∞ —Å—É —É —Ç–æ –≤—Ä–µ–º–µ —Ä–∞–¥–∏–ª–∏ —É –¥—Ä—É–≥–∏–º –¥—Ä–∂–∞–≤–∞–º–∞? –ö–æ–º—É–Ω–∏–∑–∞–º –∏ –ø–ª—É—Ç–æ–∫—Ä–∞—Ç–∏—ò–∞ (–∑–∞—ò–µ–¥–Ω–æ —Å–∞ –≥–ª–æ–±–∞–ª–∏–∑–∞—Ü–∏—ò–æ–º) —Å—É –¥–æ–≤–µ–ª–∏ –¥–æ —Å—Ç—Ä–∞—à–Ω–µ –¥–µ–≤–∞—Å—Ç–∞—Ü–∏—ò–µ –∂–∏–≤–æ—Ç–Ω–µ —Å—Ä–µ–¥–∏–Ω–µ. –î–∞–Ω–∞—à—ö–∏ –µ–∫–æ–ª–æ–∑–∏ –∫–∞–æ —É–ø–æ–∑–æ—Ä–∞–≤–∞—ò—É –Ω–∞ —É–≥—Ä–æ–∂–µ–Ω–æ—Å—Ç –µ–≥–∑–∏—Å—Ç–µ–Ω—Ü–∏—ò–µ –Ω–µ–∫–∏—Ö –≤—Ä—Å—Ç–∞ –∂–∏–≤–æ—Ç–∏—ö–∞. –ê–ª–∏ –Ω–∏–∫–∞–∫–æ –Ω–µ–º–æ–≥—É –¥–∞ —Å—Ö–≤–∞—Ç–µ –¥–∞ —ò–µ –∏—Å—Ç–æ —Ç–∞–∫–æ —É–≥—Ä–æ–∂–µ–Ω–∞ —Å–∞–º–∞ –µ–≥–∑–∏—Å—Ç–µ–Ω—Ü–∏—ò–∞ –Ω–∞—à–µ —Å–æ–ø—Å—Ç–≤–µ–Ω–µ –±–µ–ª–µ —Ä–∞—Å–µ. –°–≤–∏ –∑–Ω–∞—ò—É –¥–∞ —ò–µ –ø—Ä–æ—Ç–∏–≤–ø—Ä–∏—Ä–æ–¥–Ω–æ –º–µ—à–∞—ö–µ —à–∏–º–ø–∞–Ω–∑–∞ –∏ –≥–æ—Ä–∏–ª–µ. –ê–ª–∏ –º–µ—à–∞—ö–µ –±–µ–ª–∞—Ü–∞ –∏ –¥—Ä—É–≥–∏—Ö —Ä–∞—Å–∞ —ò–µ –∑–∞ —ö–∏—Ö –Ω–æ—Ä–º–∞–ª–Ω–æ, —á–∞–∫ –∏ –ø–æ–∂–µ—ô–Ω–æ. –ú–∏ –±—Ä–∞–Ω–∏–º–æ –Ω–∞—à–µ –ø—Ä–∏—Ä–æ–¥–Ω–æ –∏ —É—Å—Ç–∞–≤–Ω–æ –ø—Ä–∞–≤–æ –Ω–∞ –∑–¥—Ä–∞–≤—ô–µ –∏ –æ–ø—Å—Ç–∞–Ω–∞–∫, –Ω–∏–∫–æ –Ω–∞–º —Ç–æ –Ω–µ —Å–º–µ —É–≥—Ä–æ–∑–∏—Ç–∏ –±–∏–ª–æ –∏–∑ –∫–æ–≥ —Ä–∞–∑–ª–æ–≥–∞. –ù–µ –ø–æ—Å—Ç–æ—ò–∏ –ø–∞—Ç—Ä–∏–æ—Ç–∏–∑–∞–º –±–µ–∑ –µ–∫–æ–ª–æ–≥–∏—ò–µ, –Ω–∏—Ç–∏ –µ–∫–æ–ª–æ–≥–∏—ò–∞ –±–µ–∑ –ø–∞—Ç—Ä–∏–æ—Ç–∏–∑–º–∞, –∑–∞—Ç–æ —ò–µ –≤—Ä—Ö—É–Ω—Å–∫–∏ —Ü–∏—ô –ø–∞—Ç—Ä–∏–æ—Ç–∏–∑–º–∞ –∑–∞—à—Ç–∏—Ç–∞ –∂–∏–≤–æ—Ç–Ω–µ —Å—Ä–µ–¥–∏–Ω–µ. üá¨üáß Ecology is one of the basic foundations of our path. Thought has always been based on natural laws. Today's ecologists, mostly anarchists and communists, say that ecology is their invention. But it's not a rock. In the German Reich, the principle of blood and soil was propagated, young men from youth cooperatives were constantly in nature, their leader himself, although he ate food of animal origin - leaned towards a veterinary diet (eggs, cheese, milk and fruit/vegetables), loved animals and often lived in the mountains. Germany was the first country with laws on nature protection. And what were they doing in other countries at that time? Communism and plutocracy (along with globalization) have led to terrible environmental devastation. Today's ecologists are warning about the threat to the existence of some species of animals. But they cannot possibly understand that the very existence of our own white race is also threatened. Everyone knows that mixing chimpanzees and gorillas is unnatural. But the mixing of whites and other races is normal for them, even desirable. We defend our natural and constitutional right to health and survival, no one can threaten us for any reason. There is no patriotism without ecology, nor ecology without patriotism, that is why the ultimate goal of patriotism is environmental protection.

üá∑üá∏ –î–µ–º–æ–∫—Ä–∞—Ç–∏—ò–∞ –≤–∞–º –Ω—É–¥–∏ —à–∏—Ä–æ–∫ –∏–∑–±–æ—Ä –∏–∑–±–æ—Ä–∞. –ê–ª–∏ –∞–∫–æ —Å—É —Å–≤–∏ –æ–≤–∏ –∏–∑–±–æ—Ä–∏ –æ—Ç—Ä–æ–≤, —à—Ç–∞ —á–æ–≤–µ–∫ –º–æ–∂–µ —É—á–∏–Ω–∏—Ç–∏ –æ—Å–∏–º –¥–∞ –∏—Ö —É–Ω–∏—à—Ç–∏? –ò –∫–∞–∫–æ —Å–µ —É–Ω–∏—à—Ç–∞–≤–∞? –£–Ω–∏—à—Ç–∞–≤–∞—Ç–µ –ø–ª–∞—Ç—Ñ–æ—Ä–º—É –∫–æ—ò–∞ –ø–æ–¥—Ä–∂–∞–≤–∞ –æ–≤–µ –æ—Ç—Ä–æ–≤–µ; –º–∞–ª–æ –ø–æ –º–∞–ª–æ, —Ü–µ–Ω—Ç–∏–º–µ—Ç–∞—Ä –ø–æ –∏–Ω—á. –ê–∫–æ —ò–µ –∏—à—Ç–∞ –≤—Ä–µ–¥–Ω–∏—ò–µ –æ–¥ –æ–≤–∏—Ö –æ—Ç—Ä–æ–≤–∞ - –æ–≤–∏—Ö –ø–æ–ª–∏—Ç–∏—á–∞—Ä–∞ - –∫–æ—ò–µ –º–æ—Ä–∞–º–æ –¥–∞ "–∏–∑–∞–±–µ—Ä–µ–º–æ", —Ç–æ —ò–µ —Å–∏—Å—Ç–µ–º –∫–æ—ò–∏ –∏–º –¥–æ–∑–≤–æ—ô–∞–≤–∞ –∏ –ø–æ–¥—Å—Ç–∏—á–µ –∏—Ö –¥–∞ –Ω–∞–ø—Ä–µ–¥—É—ò—É —Å–∞ –Ω–∞—à–∏—Ö –ª–µ—í–∞. üá¨üáß Democracy offers you a wide variety of choices. But if all these choices are poison, what can man do but destroy them? And how is it destroyed? You destroy the platform that supports these poisons; little by little, centimeter by inch. If anything is more valuable than these poisons - these politicians - that we have to "elect", it is the system that allows and encourages them to thrive off our backs.

üá∑üá∏ –ú–æ—Ä–∞–º–æ —Ä–µ—õ–∏ –¥–∞ —ò–µ —Ä–µ–≤–æ–ª—É—Ü–∏–æ–Ω–∞—Ä –æ—Å—É—í–µ–Ω –Ω–∞ –ø—Ä–æ–ø–∞—Å—Ç. –û–Ω –Ω–µ–º–∞ –ø—Ä–∏–≤–∞—Ç–Ω–µ –∏–Ω—Ç–µ—Ä–µ—Å–µ, –Ω–µ–º–∞ –∞—Ñ–µ—Ä–∞, –æ—Å–µ—õ–∞—ö–∞ –ø—Ä–µ–º–∞ –Ω–µ–ø—Ä–∏—ò–∞—Ç–µ—ô–∏–º–∞, –∏–º–æ–≤–∏–Ω—É, –ø–∞ —á–∞–∫ –Ω–∏ —Å–≤–æ—ò–µ –∏–º–µ. –ß–∏—Ç–∞–≤–æ —ö–µ–≥–æ–≤–æ –±–∏—õ–µ –ø—Ä–æ–∂–¥–∏—Ä–µ —ò–µ–¥–Ω–∞ —Å–≤—Ä—Ö–∞, —ò–µ–¥–Ω–∞ –º–∏—Å–∞–æ, —ò–µ–¥–Ω–∞ —Å—Ç—Ä–∞—Å—Ç ‚Äì —Ä–µ–≤–æ–ª—É—Ü–∏—ò–∞. –°—Ä—Ü–µ–º –∏ –¥—É—à–æ–º, –Ω–µ —Å–∞–º–æ —Ä–µ—á—ò—É –≤–µ—õ –¥–µ–ª–æ–º, –ø—Ä–µ–∫–∏–Ω—É–æ —ò–µ —Å–≤–∞–∫—É –≤–µ–∑—É —Å–∞ –¥—Ä—É—à—Ç–≤–µ–Ω–∏–º –ø–æ—Ä–µ—Ç–∫–æ–º –∏ —Å–∞ —Ü–µ–ª–∏–º —Ü–∏–≤–∏–ª–∏–∑–æ–≤–∞–Ω–∏–º —Å–≤–µ—Ç–æ–º; —Å–∞ –∑–∞–∫–æ–Ω–∏–º–∞, –¥–æ–±—Ä–∏–º –º–∞–Ω–∏—Ä–∏–º–∞, –∫–æ–Ω–≤–µ–Ω—Ü–∏—ò–∞–º–∞ –∏ (–Ω–µ)–º–æ—Ä–∞–ª–æ–º —Ç–æ–≥ —Å–≤–µ—Ç–∞. –û–Ω —ò–µ —ö–µ–Ω –Ω–µ–º–∏–ª–æ—Å—Ä–¥–Ω–∏ –Ω–µ–ø—Ä–∏—ò–∞—Ç–µ—ô –∏ –Ω–∞—Å—Ç–∞–≤—ô–∞ –¥–∞ –≥–∞ –Ω–∞—Å–µ—ô–∞–≤–∞ —Å–∞–º–æ —Å–∞ —ò–µ–¥–Ω–∏–º —Ü–∏—ô–µ–º ‚Äì –¥–∞ –≥–∞ —É–Ω–∏—à—Ç–∏. üá¨üáß We must say that the revolutionary is doomed. He has no private interests, no affairs, no property, and not even his own name. His whole being is consumed by one purpose, one thought, one passion - revolution. With heart and soul, not only in word but in deed, he severed all connection with the social order and with the whole civilized world; with the laws, good manners, conventions and (im)morality of that world. He is her merciless enemy and continues to inhabit it with only one goal - to destroy it. He must also incite the people to revolt, to show them the truth and the right way.

üá∑üá∏ –ù–∞—Ü–∏–æ–Ω–∞–ª–Ω–∞ —Ä–µ–≤–æ–ª—É—Ü–∏—ò–∞! –†–∞–¥, –ø–æ—Ä–æ–¥–∏—Ü–∞, –¥–æ–º–æ–≤–∏–Ω–∞! –ü–æ—Å—Ç–µ—Ä –í–∏—à–∏—ò–µ–≤—Å–∫–µ –§—Ä–∞–Ω—Ü—É—Å–∫–µ –∫–æ—ò–∏ —É–ø–æ—Ä–µ—í—É—ò–µ –±–µ–∑–±–µ–¥–Ω–æ—Å—Ç –∫—É—õ–µ –∏–∑–≥—Ä–∞—í–µ–Ω–µ –Ω–∞ –ø—Ä–∏–Ω—Ü–∏–ø–∏–º–∞ –ù–∞—Ü–∏–æ–Ω–∞–ª–Ω–µ —Ä–µ–≤–æ–ª—É—Ü–∏—ò–µ —Å–∞ –Ω–µ—Å–∏–≥—É—Ä–Ω–æ—à—õ—É –∫—É—õ–µ –∑–∞—Å–Ω–æ–≤–∞–Ω–µ –Ω–∞ ‚Äû–ª–µ—ö–æ—Å—Ç–∏‚Äú, ‚Äû–¥–µ–º–∞–≥–æ–≥–∏—ò–∏‚Äú –∏ ‚Äû–∏–Ω—Ç–µ—Ä–Ω–∞—Ü–∏–æ–Ω–∞–ª–∏–∑–º—É‚Äú. üá¨üáß National revolution! Work, family, homeland! Vichy France poster comparing the security of a house built on the principles of the National Revolution to the insecurity of a house based on "laziness", "demagoguery" and "internationalism".

üá∑üá∏ –í–∏ –∫–∞–æ —Å–ª–µ–¥–±–µ–Ω–∏–∫ —Ä–µ–≤–æ–ª—É—Ü–∏–æ–Ω–∞—Ä–Ω–æ–≥ –∏–¥–µ–∞–ª–∏–∑–º–∞ –º–æ—Ä–∞—Ç–µ –Ω–∞—Å—Ç–∞–≤–∏—Ç–∏ –Ω–∞—Å–ª–µ—í–µ –Ω–∞—à–∏—Ö –ø—Ä–µ–¥–∞–∫–∞. –†–∞—Ç –ø—Ä–æ—Ç–∏–≤ –Ω–∞—à–∏—Ö –Ω–µ–ø—Ä–∏—ò–∞—Ç–µ—ô–∞ —ò–µ —É –Ω–∞—à–µ–º –î–ù–ö, —Ä–∞–¥–∏ —Å–µ –æ –æ–¥–±—Ä–∞–Ω–∏ —Ä–∞—Åe –∏ –æ–Ω–∏—Ö –∫–æ—ò–µ –≤–æ–ª–∏—Ç–µ. –ü–æ—Ç–ø—É–Ω–æ —É–Ω–∏—à—Ç–∞–≤–∞—ö–µ –ø—Ä–µ—Ç—ö–∏ –Ω–∏—ò–µ –Ω–∏—à—Ç–∞ –¥—Ä—É–≥–æ –¥–æ —Å–∞–º–æ–æ–¥–±—Ä–∞–Ω–∞ –æ–¥ —Å—Ç—Ä–∞–Ω–µ –ù–∞—Ü–∏–æ–Ω–∞–ª–∏—Å—Ç–∞. –ü–∞–¥–æ–≤–∏ –Ω–∞—à–∏—Ö –ø—Ä–µ–¥–∞–∫–∞, –æ—á–µ–≤–∞, –¥–µ–¥–æ–≤–∞ –∏ –ø–æ—Å–µ–±–Ω–æ –±—Ä–∞—õ–µ –ø–æ –∫—Ä–≤–∏ –∫–æ—ò–∏ —Å—É —Å–µ —Ö—Ä–∞–±—Ä–æ –±–æ—Ä–∏–ª–∏ –¥–æ –∫—Ä–∞—ò–∞, –æ—Å—É–¥–∏–ª–∏ —Å—É —Ç—Ä–∫—É. –ú–∏ —Å–º–æ —Å–∞–¥–∞ –æ–¥–≥–æ–≤–æ—Ä–Ω–∏ –∑–∞ –æ–≤–∞—ò –ø—Ä–æ—à–∏—Ä–µ–Ω–∏ —Ä–∞—Ç, –Ω–µ —Å–∞–º–æ —Ñ–∏–∑–∏—á–∫–∏, –≤–µ—õ –∏ –∫—É–ª—Ç—É—Ä–Ω–æ –∏ –¥—É—Ö–æ–≤–Ω–æ. –°–≤–∞–∫–æ –æ–¥ –Ω–∞—Å –º–æ—Ä–∞ –∞–∫—Ç–∏–≤–Ω–æ –¥–∞ —Å–∞—Ä–∞—í—É—ò–µ —É –∏–º–µ —Å–≤–æ–≥ –Ω–∞—Ä–æ–¥–∞, –∫–∞–æ —à—Ç–æ —Å—É —Ç–æ —á–∏–Ω–∏–ª–∏ –∏ –æ–Ω–∏ –ø—Ä–µ –Ω–∞—Å. üá¨üáß You, as a follower of revolutionary idealism, must continue the legacy of our ancestors. War against our enemies is in our DNA, it's about defending the race and the ones you love. The complete destruction of threats is nothing more than self-defense by the Nationalists. The falls of our ancestors, fathers, grandfathers and especially blood brothers who fought bravely to the end, condemned the race. We are now responsible for this extended war, not only physically, but also culturally and spiritually. Each of us must actively cooperate on behalf of our people, as they did before us.

üá∑üá∏ –¶–µ–ª–æ–∫—É–ø–Ω–æ –≤–∞—Å–ø–∏—Ç–∞—ö–µ –º–æ—Ä–∞ –¥–∞ –±—É–¥–µ —É—Å—Ç—Ä–æ—ò–µ–Ω–æ —Ç–∞–∫–æ –¥–∞ —Å–µ —Å–ª–æ–±–æ–¥–Ω–æ –≤—Ä–µ–º–µ –æ–º–ª–∞–¥–∏–Ω—Ü–∞ —É–ø–æ—Ç—Ä–µ–±–∏ –∑–∞ –∫–æ—Ä–∏—Å—Ç–∞–Ω —Ä–∞–∑–≤–æ—ò —ö–µ–≥–æ–≤–æ–≥ —Ç–µ–ª–∞. –û–Ω –Ω–µ–º–∞ –Ω–∏–∫–∞–∫–≤–æ –ø—Ä–∞–≤–æ –¥–∞ —É —Ç–∏–º –≥–æ–¥–∏–Ω–∞–º–∞ –¥–æ–∫–æ–Ω–æ –≥–ª—É–≤–∞—Ä–∏, –≤–µ—õ —Ç—Ä–µ–±–∞ –ø–æ—Å–ª–µ —Å–≤–æ–≥ —É–æ–±–∏—á–∞—ò–µ–Ω–æ–≥ –¥–Ω–µ–≤–Ω–æ–≥ –ø–æ—Å–ª–∞ –¥–∞ —á–µ–ª–∏—á–∏ —Å–≤–æ—ò–µ —Ç–µ–ª–æ –∏ —É—á–∏–Ω–∏ –≥–∞ —Å–Ω–∞–∂–Ω–∏–º, –¥–∞ –≥–∞ –Ω–µ –±–∏ —ò–µ–¥–Ω–æ–º –∏ –∂–∏–≤–æ—Ç –∑–∞—Ç–µ–∫–∞–æ —Å—É–≤–∏—à–µ –º–µ–∫–∞–Ω–æ–≥. –û–≤–æ –∏—Å–ø–ª–∞–Ω–∏—Ä–∞—Ç–∏ –∏ —Å–ø—Ä–æ–≤–µ—Å—Ç–∏, —É—Å–º–µ—Ä–∞–≤–∞—Ç–∏ –∏ –≤–æ–¥–∏—Ç–∏, –∑–∞–¥–∞—Ç–∞–∫ —ò–µ –≤–∞—Å–ø–∏—Ç–∞—ö–∞ –º–ª–∞–¥–∏—Ö, –∞ –Ω–µ –∏—Å–∫—ô—É—á–∏–≤–æ —É–ø—É–º–ø–∞–≤–∞—ö–µ —Ç–∞–∫–æ–∑–≤–∞–Ω–æ–≥ –∑–Ω–∞—ö–∞. –û–º–ª–∞–¥–∏–Ω–∞—Ü —Ç–∞–∫–æ—í–µ —Ç—Ä–µ–±–∞ –¥–∞ –æ–¥—Å—Ç—Ä–∞–Ω–∏ –ø—Ä–µ–¥—Å—Ç–∞–≤—É –∫–∞–æ –¥–∞ —ò–µ –±–∞–≤—ô–µ—ö–µ —Å–≤–æ—ò–∏–º —Ç–µ–ª–æ–º –ª–∏—á–Ω–∞ —Å—Ç–≤–∞—Ä —Å–≤–∞–∫–æ–≥ –ø–æ—ò–µ–¥–∏–Ω—Ü–∞. –ù–µ –ø–æ—Å—Ç–æ—ò–∏ –Ω–∏–∫–∞–∫–≤–∞ —Å–ª–æ–±–æ–¥–∞ –∫–æ—ò–∞ –æ–º–æ–≥—É—õ–∞–≤–∞ –¥–∞ —Å–µ –≥—Ä–µ—à–∏ –Ω–∞ —Ä–∞—á—É–Ω –ø–æ—Ç–æ–º—Å—Ç–≤–∞, –∞ —Ç–∏–º–µ –∏ –Ω–∞—Ü–∏—ò–µ. üá¨üáß The whole upbringing must be built in so that the free time of the youth is used for the use of his body. He has no right to be idle at that age, but should, after his usual daily work, take care of his body and make it strong, so that life does not find him too soft. To plan and implement this, to direct and lead, is the task of educating young people, and not exclusively pumping in so-called knowledge. A young person should also remove the notion that dealing with his body is a personal matter for each individual. There is no freedom that allows one to make mistakes at the expense of posterity and thus the nation.

Day by day, we sink as a nation deeper and deeper into the slime and ruin of a modern society orchestrated by Zionists and their servants. So the death and extermination of our race, and with it our nation, is inevitable, unless something radically urgent is taken! Today, a Serb, as a racial idealist and a proud nationalist, will be condemned from the outset to persecution and discrimination, because of his actions and the assertion of his race and nationality. The media has been so successful in degenerating the racial movement itself, not only in us, but in the world, that it has become the subject of general ridicule, or in some cases, a potential danger to the "stability and happiness" of this decrepit and rotten social order. That's why our comrades were persecuted, that's why many earlier attempts to launch any kind of racial-nationalist narrative were sanctioned by the authorities. The modern world does not tolerate white pride and our ancient Aryan values. There will always be those who will sell themselves to Jewish masters for trinkets and cottages, and thus betray their race and nation. They come first when it comes to our enemies. First we must separate the wheat from the chaff, and the foes in our ranks must be eliminated. Idealism is what drives us! We will not compromise with "nationalists" and "conservatives" in Serbia who have long since sold themselves to the authorities for political careers. We will not fall for the coasters and the quasi-nationalistic, even the chauvinist floscouses and games again. Our only task is to point out to our people a problem that could cost the heads of anyone who indulges in personal and present pleasures. Our sacred mission is, above all, to put the white Serb youth back on the right path of truth, honour, freedom, and heroism.

üá∑üá∏ –î–í–ï –°–¢–†–ê–°–¢–ò –°—Ç—Ä–∞—Å—Ç –¥–æ–ª–∞–∑–∏ —É –¥–≤–∞ –æ–±–ª–∏–∫–∞. –à–µ–¥–Ω–æ —ò–µ –º–ª–∞–¥–∞–ª–∞—á–∫–∞ —Å—Ç—Ä–∞—Å—Ç, –∞ –¥—Ä—É–≥–æ –∏—Å—Ç–∏–Ω—Å–∫–∞ —Å—Ç—Ä–∞—Å—Ç. –ú–ª–∞–¥–∞—á–∫–∞ —Å—Ç—Ä–∞—Å—Ç —ò–µ —É –Ω–∞—ò–±–æ—ô–µ–º —Å–ª—É—á–∞—ò—É –Ω–∞–∏–≤–Ω–æ—Å—Ç –∏–ª–∏ —Å–∞–º–æ–æ–±–º–∞–Ω–∞ —É –Ω–∞—ò–≥–æ—Ä–µ–º. –¢–æ —ò–µ —Å—Ç—Ä–∞—Å—Ç –∫–æ—ò–∞ –Ω–∞—Å—Ç–∞—ò–µ –∏–∑ –Ω–µ–∏—Å–∫—É—Å—Ç–≤–∞ –∏ –Ω–∞–¥–µ. –î–∞–∫–ª–µ, —Ç–æ —ò–µ —Å—Ç—Ä–∞—Å—Ç –∫–æ—ò–∞ —Å–µ –ª–∞–∫–æ –≥–∞—Å–∏ –∫–∞–¥–∞ —Å–µ —Å—É–æ—á–∏ —Å–∞ —Å—É—Ä–æ–≤–æ—Å—Ç–∏–º–∞ –∂–∏–≤–æ—Ç–∞. –° –¥—Ä—É–≥–µ —Å—Ç—Ä–∞–Ω–µ, –∏—Å–∫—Ä–µ–Ω–∞ —Å—Ç—Ä–∞—Å—Ç —ò–µ —Å—É–º–ø–æ—Ä–Ω–∏ –∏ –Ω–µ–º–∏–ª–æ—Å—Ä–¥–Ω–∏ –≥–Ω–µ–≤ –í–æ—ô–∞ –∏—Å–∫–æ–≤–∞–Ω–∞ –∏–∑ –º—Ä–∞—á–Ω–æ–≥ —Ä–∞–∑—É–º–µ–≤–∞—ö–∞ –ø—É—Ç–∞—ö–µ —Å–∞–≤—Ä–µ–º–µ–Ω–æ–≥ —Å–≤–µ—Ç–∞. –î–∞–∫–ª–µ, —Ç–æ —ò–µ —Å—Ç—Ä–∞—Å—Ç –∫–æ—ò–∞ –º–æ–∂–µ –¥–∞ –∏–∑–¥—Ä–∂–∏ —Ö–∏—ô–∞–¥—É –µ–∫—Å–ø–ª–æ–∑–∏—ò–∞, –∞ –¥–∞ –∏–ø–∞–∫ –∏–∑–∞—í–µ –Ω–µ–ø–æ–≤—Ä–µ—í–µ–Ω–∞. –¢–æ —ò–µ –∏—Å—Ç–∞ —Å—Ç—Ä–∞—Å—Ç –∫–æ—ò—É —Å—É –ø–æ—Å–µ–¥–æ–≤–∞–ª–∏ –•–∏—Ç–ª–µ—Ä, –ú—É—Å–æ–ª–∏–Ω–∏, –ú–æ–∑–ª–∏, –ö–æ–¥—Ä–µ–∞–Ω—É, –î–µ –†–∏–≤–µ—Ä–∞ –∏ –º–Ω–æ–≥–µ –¥—Ä—É–≥–µ —Ä–µ–≤–æ–ª—É—Ü–∏–æ–Ω–∞—Ä–Ω–µ –Ω–∞—Ü–∏–æ–Ω–∞–ª–∏—Å—Ç–∏—á–∫–µ –ª–∏—á–Ω–æ—Å—Ç–∏. –¢–æ —ò–µ —Å—Ç—Ä–∞—Å—Ç –∫–æ—ò–∞ —ò–µ, —É–ø—Ä–∫–æ—Å —Ç–µ–ª–µ—Å–Ω–æ–º –∏—Å—Ç–µ–∫—É —Å–≤–æ—ò–∏—Ö –ø–æ—Å–µ–¥–Ω–∏–∫–∞, —ò–æ—à —É–≤–µ–∫ —Å–∏–ª–∞ –Ω–∞ –∫–æ—ò—É —Ç—Ä–µ–±–∞ —Ä–∞—á—É–Ω–∞—Ç–∏; —ò–æ—à —É–≤–µ–∫ —ò–µ –¥–µ—Ç–æ–Ω–∞—Ü–∏—ò–∞ —Å–Ω–∞–≥–µ, –º–æ—õ–∏ –∏ —Ä–∞–¥–æ—Å—Ç–∏; —ò–µ —ò–æ—à —É–≤–µ–∫ –º–∞–Ω–∏—Ñ–µ—Å—Ç–∞—Ü–∏—ò–∞ —Å–∞–º–µ –ø—Ä–∏—Ä–æ–¥–µ –∫–æ—ò–∞ —É–Ω–∞–ø—Ä–µ—í—É—ò–µ —Å–≤–æ—ò—É –≤–ª–∞–¥–∞–≤–∏–Ω—É. –û–≤–æ —ò–µ —Å—Ç—Ä–∞—Å—Ç –∫–æ—ò—É –ø–æ—Å–µ–¥—É—ò—É –∏ –º–ª–∞–¥–∏ –∏ —Å—Ç–∞—Ä–∏. –î–∞–∫–ª–µ, –æ–≤–æ —ò–µ —Å—Ç—Ä–∞—Å—Ç ‚Äì –í–æ—ô–∞ ‚Äì –∫–æ—ò–∞ –Ω–∞—Å—Ç–∞–≤—ô–∞ –¥–∞ –Ω–∞–ø—Ä–µ–¥—É—ò–µ —Ç–æ–∫–æ–º –≤—Ä–µ–º–µ–Ω–∞ –∏ –Ω–∏–∫–∞–¥–∞ –Ω–µ –º–æ–∂–µ –±–∏—Ç–∏ –∑–∞–∏—Å—Ç–∞ –ø–æ—Ä–∞–∂–µ–Ω–∞ –∏–ª–∏ —É–±–∏—ò–µ–Ω–∞; —Å–∞–º–æ —Ç—Ä–µ–Ω—É—Ç–Ω–æ –æ–º–µ—Ç–∞–Ω–æ. –¢–æ —ò–µ –∏—Å—Ç–∞ —Å—Ç—Ä–∞—Å—Ç –∫–æ—ò—É —Å–≤–∞–∫–∏ –Ω–∞—Ü–∏–æ–Ω–∞–ª–∏—Å—Ç–∞ –≤—Ä–µ–¥–∞–Ω —Å–≤–æ—ò–µ —Å–æ–ª–∏ —Ç–∞–∫–æ—í–µ –º–æ—Ä–∞ –ø–æ—Å–µ–¥–æ–≤–∞—Ç–∏ –∏ —ö–æ–º–µ –±–∏—Ç–∏ –ø–æ—Å–µ–¥–Ω—É—Ç. üá¨üáß THE TWO PASSIONS Passion comes in two forms. One is youthful passion and the other is genuine passion. Youthful passion is naivety at best or self-deceit at worst. It is a passion that arises out of inexperience and hopefulness. Thus, it is a passion that is easily snuffed out when confronted with the cruelties of life. Genuine passion on the other hand is a sulfuric and relentless wrath of Will forged from a grim understanding of the modern world's trajectory. Thus, it is a passion that can withstand one thousand blasts yet still come out unscathed regardless. This is the same passion that Hitler, Mussolini, Mosley, Codreanu, De Rivera and many more revolutionary nationalists figures all possessed. This is the passion that, despite the bodily expiration of its possessors, is still a force to be reckoned with; is still a detonation of strength, power, and joy; is still a manifestation of Nature herself advancing her rule. This is the passion that both the young and old possess. Therefore, this is a passion ‚Äì a Will ‚Äì that continues to advance itself throughout time and can never truly be defeated or killed; only albeit momentarily hindered. This is the same passion that every nationalist worth their salt must likewise possess and be possessed by it.

üá∑üá∏ ‚Äû–à–µ–¥–∞–Ω –Ω–∞—Ä–æ–¥ –≤–µ—á–Ω–æ –∂–∏–≤–∏ –∫—Ä–æ–∑ —Å–≤–æ—ò–µ –∫–æ–Ω—Ü–µ–ø—Ç–µ, —á–∞—Å—Ç –∏ –∫—É–ª—Ç—É—Ä—É. –£–ø—Ä–∞–≤–æ –∏–∑ —Ç–∏—Ö —Ä–∞–∑–ª–æ–≥–∞ –≤–ª–∞–¥–∞—Ä–∏ –Ω–∞—Ü–∏—ò–∞ –º–æ—Ä–∞—ò—É –¥–∞ —Å—É–¥–µ –∏ –¥–µ–ª—É—ò—É –Ω–µ —Å–∞–º–æ –Ω–∞ –æ—Å–Ω–æ–≤—É —Ñ–∏–∑–∏—á–∫–∏—Ö –∏ –º–∞—Ç–µ—Ä–∏—ò–∞–ª–Ω–∏—Ö –∏–Ω—Ç–µ—Ä–µ—Å–∞ –Ω–∞—Ü–∏—ò–µ, –≤–µ—õ –∏ –Ω–∞ –æ—Å–Ω–æ–≤—É –∏—Å—Ç–æ—Ä–∏—ò—Å–∫–µ —á–∞—Å—Ç–∏ –Ω–∞—Ü–∏—ò–µ. , –≤–µ—á–Ω–∏—Ö –∏–Ω—Ç–µ—Ä–µ—Å–∞ –Ω–∞—Ü–∏—ò–µ. –î–∞–∫–ª–µ: –Ω–µ —Ö–ª–µ–± –ø–æ —Å–≤–∞–∫—É —Ü–µ–Ω—É, –Ω–µ–≥–æ —á–∞—Å—Ç –ø–æ —Å–≤–∞–∫—É —Ü–µ–Ω—É‚Äú. ‚Äî –ö–æ—Ä–Ω–µ–ª–∏—ò—É –ó–µ–ª–µ–∞ –ö–æ–¥—Ä–µ–∞–Ω—É –ù–∞ –¥–∞–Ω–∞—à—ö–∏ –¥–∞–Ω —Ä–æ—í–µ–Ω —ò–µ –Ω–∞—Ü–∏–æ–Ω–∞–ª–∏—Å—Ç–∞ –∏ –æ—Å–Ω–∏–≤–∞—á –õ–µ–≥–∏—ò–µ –∞—Ä—Ö–∞–Ω—í–µ–ª–∞ –ú–∏—Ö–∞–∏–ª–∞ –∏–ª–∏ –∏–Ω–∞—á–µ –ø–æ–∑–Ω–∞—Ç–∏—ò–µ–≥ –∫–∞–æ –ì–≤–æ–∑–¥–µ–Ω–∞ –≥–∞—Ä–¥–∞, –ö–æ—Ä–Ω–µ–ª–∏—ò—É –ó–µ–ª–µ–∞ –ö–æ–¥—Ä–µ–∞–Ω—É. üá¨üáß "A nation lives forever through its concepts, honor, and culture. It is for these reasons that the rulers of nations must judge and act not only on the basis of physical and material interests of the nation but on the basis of the nation's historical honor, of the nation's eternal interests. Thus: not bread at all costs, but honor at all costs." ‚Äî Corneliu Zelea Codreanu On this day, the nationalist and founder of the Legion of the Archangel Michael or otherwise known as the Iron Guard, Cornelius Zelea Codreanu, was born.

üá∑üá∏ –ï–∫–æ–ª–æ–≥–∏—ò–∞ —ò–µ —ò–µ–¥–∞–Ω –æ–¥ –æ—Å–Ω–æ–≤–Ω–∏—Ö —Ç–µ–º–µ—ô–∞ –Ω–∞—à–µ–≥ –ø—É—Ç–∞. –ú–∏—Å–∞–æ —ò–µ —É–≤–µ–∫ –±–∏–ª–∞ –∑–∞—Å–Ω–æ–≤–∞–Ω–∞ –Ω–∞ –ø—Ä–∏—Ä–æ–¥–Ω–∏–º –∑–∞–∫–æ–Ω–∏–º–∞. –î–∞–Ω–∞—à—ö–∏ –µ–∫–æ–ª–æ–∑–∏, –º–∞—Ö–æ–º –∞–Ω–∞—Ä—Ö–∏—Å—Ç–∏ –∏ –∫–æ–º—É–Ω–∏—Å—Ç–∏, –∫–∞–∂—É –¥–∞ —ò–µ –µ–∫–æ–ª–æ–≥–∏—ò–∞ —ö–∏—Ö–æ–≤ –ø—Ä–æ–Ω–∞–ª–∞–∑–∞–∫. –ê–ª–∏ —Ç–æ –Ω–∏—ò–µ —Å—Ç–∏–Ω–∞. –£ –ù–µ–º–∞—á–∫–æ–º —Ä–∞—ò—Ö—É —ò–µ –ø—Ä–æ–ø–∞–≥–∏—Ä–∞–Ω –ø—Ä–∏–Ω—Ü–∏–ø –∫—Ä–≤–∏ –∏ —Ç–ª–∞, –º–ª–∞–¥–∏—õ–∏ –∏–∑ –æ–º–ª–∞–¥–∏–Ω—Å–∫–∏—Ö –∑–∞–¥—Ä—É–≥–∞ —Å—É —Å—Ç–∞–ª–Ω–æ –±–æ—Ä–∞–≤–∏–ª–∏ —É –ø—Ä–∏—Ä–æ–¥–∏, —Å–∞–º —ö–∏—Ö–æ–≤ –≤–æ—í–∞ –∏–∞–∫–æ —ò–µ —ò–µ–æ —Ö—Ä–∞–Ω—É –∂–∏–≤–æ—Ç–∏—ö—Å–∫–æ–≥ –ø–æ—Ä–µ–∫–ª–∞ - –Ω–∞–≥–∏—ö–∞–æ –≤–µ—Ç–µ—Ä–∏—ò–∞–Ω—Å–∫–æ–º –Ω–∞—á–∏–Ω—É –∏—Å—Ö—Ä–∞–Ω–µ(—ò–∞—ò–∞,—Å–∏—Ä,–º–ª–µ–∫–æ –∏ –≤–æ—õ–µ/–ø–æ–≤—Ä—õ–µ), –≤–æ–ª–µ–æ –∂–∏–≤–æ—Ç–∏—ö–µ –∏ —á–µ—Å—Ç–æ –±–æ—Ä–∞–≤–∏–æ —É –ø–ª–∞–Ω–∏–Ω–∞–º–∞. –ù–µ–º–∞—á–∫–∞ —ò–µ –±–∏–ª–∞ –ø—Ä–≤–∞ –∑–µ–º—ô–∞ —Å–∞ –∑–∞–∫–æ–Ω–∏–º–∞ –Ω–∞ –∑–∞—à—Ç–∏—Ç—É –ø—Ä–∏—Ä–æ–¥–µ. –ê —à—Ç–∞ —Å—É —É —Ç–æ –≤—Ä–µ–º–µ —Ä–∞–¥–∏–ª–∏ —É –¥—Ä—É–≥–∏–º –¥—Ä–∂–∞–≤–∞–º–∞? –ö–æ–º—É–Ω–∏–∑–∞–º –∏ –ø–ª—É—Ç–æ–∫—Ä–∞—Ç–∏—ò–∞ (–∑–∞—ò–µ–¥–Ω–æ —Å–∞ –≥–ª–æ–±–∞–ª–∏–∑–∞—Ü–∏—ò–æ–º) —Å—É –¥–æ–≤–µ–ª–∏ –¥–æ —Å—Ç—Ä–∞—à–Ω–µ –¥–µ–≤–∞—Å—Ç–∞—Ü–∏—ò–µ –∂–∏–≤–æ—Ç–Ω–µ —Å—Ä–µ–¥–∏–Ω–µ. –î–∞–Ω–∞—à—ö–∏ –µ–∫–æ–ª–æ–∑–∏ –∫–∞–æ —É–ø–æ–∑–æ—Ä–∞–≤–∞—ò—É –Ω–∞ —É–≥—Ä–æ–∂–µ–Ω–æ—Å—Ç –µ–≥–∑–∏—Å—Ç–µ–Ω—Ü–∏—ò–µ –Ω–µ–∫–∏—Ö –≤—Ä—Å—Ç–∞ –∂–∏–≤–æ—Ç–∏—ö–∞. –ê–ª–∏ –Ω–∏–∫–∞–∫–æ –Ω–µ–º–æ–≥—É –¥–∞ —Å—Ö–≤–∞—Ç–µ –¥–∞ —ò–µ –∏—Å—Ç–æ —Ç–∞–∫–æ —É–≥—Ä–æ–∂–µ–Ω–∞ —Å–∞–º–∞ –µ–≥–∑–∏—Å—Ç–µ–Ω—Ü–∏—ò–∞ –Ω–∞—à–µ —Å–æ–ø—Å—Ç–≤–µ–Ω–µ –±–µ–ª–µ —Ä–∞—Å–µ. –°–≤–∏ –∑–Ω–∞—ò—É –¥–∞ —ò–µ –ø—Ä–æ—Ç–∏–≤–ø—Ä–∏—Ä–æ–¥–Ω–æ –º–µ—à–∞—ö–µ —à–∏–º–ø–∞–Ω–∑–∞ –∏ –≥–æ—Ä–∏–ª–µ. –ê–ª–∏ –º–µ—à–∞—ö–µ –±–µ–ª–∞—Ü–∞ –∏ –¥—Ä—É–≥–∏—Ö —Ä–∞—Å–∞ —ò–µ –∑–∞ —ö–∏—Ö –Ω–æ—Ä–º–∞–ª–Ω–æ, —á–∞–∫ –∏ –ø–æ–∂–µ—ô–Ω–æ. –ú–∏ –±—Ä–∞–Ω–∏–º–æ –Ω–∞—à–µ –ø—Ä–∏—Ä–æ–¥–Ω–æ –∏ —É—Å—Ç–∞–≤–Ω–æ –ø—Ä–∞–≤–æ –Ω–∞ –∑–¥—Ä–∞–≤—ô–µ –∏ –æ–ø—Å—Ç–∞–Ω–∞–∫, –Ω–∏–∫–æ –Ω–∞–º —Ç–æ –Ω–µ —Å–º–µ —É–≥—Ä–æ–∑–∏—Ç–∏ –±–∏–ª–æ –∏–∑ –∫–æ–≥ —Ä–∞–∑–ª–æ–≥–∞. –ù–µ –ø–æ—Å—Ç–æ—ò–∏ –ø–∞—Ç—Ä–∏–æ—Ç–∏–∑–∞–º –±–µ–∑ –µ–∫–æ–ª–æ–≥–∏—ò–µ, –Ω–∏—Ç–∏ –µ–∫–æ–ª–æ–≥–∏—ò–∞ –±–µ–∑ –ø–∞—Ç—Ä–∏–æ—Ç–∏–∑–º–∞, –∑–∞—Ç–æ —ò–µ –≤—Ä—Ö—É–Ω—Å–∫–∏ —Ü–∏—ô –ø–∞—Ç—Ä–∏–æ—Ç–∏–∑–º–∞ –∑–∞—à—Ç–∏—Ç–∞ –∂–∏–≤–æ—Ç–Ω–µ —Å—Ä–µ–¥–∏–Ω–µ. üá¨üáß Ecology is one of the cornerstones of our journey. The thought was always based on the laws of nature. Today's environmentalists, mostly anarchists and communists, say that ecology is their invention. But that's not true. In the German Reich, the principle of blood and soil was promoted, young men from youth cooperatives were constantly in the nature, their leader himself although he ate food of animal origin - leaning towards the Weterian diet (eggs, cheese, milk and fruit / vegetables), loved animals and often stayed in the mountains. Germany was the first country with laws to protect nature. And what were they doing in other states at the time? Communism and plutocracy (along with globalization) have led to a terrible environmental devastation. Today's environmentalists are warning of the dangers of the existence of certain species of animals. But they can't possibly understand that the very existence of our own white race is also threatened. Everyone knows it's against nature to mix chimps and gorillas. The Spanish National Assemblies or Philippine Falange was a fascist, National Catholic political party in the Philippines founded by two affluent Spaniards. Initially, the party was focused on supporting Francisco Franco's regime in Spain through means, including financial donations. However, with the Japanese occupation of the Philippines during World War II, the party was forced into exile. In response to the new geopolitical situation, the Philippine Falange shifted its support to the Allies, particularly aiding the American forces in the Pacific Theater. During this period, the party established connections with General Douglas MacArthur and participated in the broader American effort against Japanese forces. P√§ts' main mistake, however, and this is how any true nationalist should critique him, not on the basis of 'he eroded muh democracy! muh liberal rights!', is that he did not see the threat of Stalin and Bolshevism in his old age. In nationalist and conservative/traditionalist circles of Estonia, there is often talk of the late President Konstantin P√§ts as a traitor. Of course, what he did to the nation in 1939-1940 is unforgiveable but we must not forget all what P√§ts, who rightfully deserves the title of 'Father of the Nation', did for Estonia's sake. In March of 1934, P√§ts with the help of General Johan Laidoner crossed the Rubicon as a Caesar and destroyed liberal democracy in Estonia, which was causing internal turmoil and political chaos. He silenced the parliament, freedom of speech was greatly limited, censorship was present in various spheres of life. P√§ts' propaganda service, the National Propaganda Service, conducted various nationalist propaganda campaigns. From 1935, the service organized an annual nationwide Mother's Day celebration, for which the Mother's Day General Committee was established in 1936. On the basis of the plan of action for the revival of folk art, approved by the State Elder, the service promoted folk costumes and folk dancing, and propaganda for the revival of folk art.In 1936, it was transferred to the competence of the Ministry of Education. In 1937, the Folk Costume Committee was established. The service took part in a home decoration campaign, the aim of the campaign was to improve the appearance of Estonian towns, villages and villages. Names of Estonians who had German or Russian names, were Estonianized. Corporatism was implemented in Estonia, but according to the criticism of some, at a limited rate. In March 1935, the activities of most political parties were banned, and unions were formed from people who supported the government - the Patriotic League, a nationalist and the professional associations (corporatist unions). The Patriotic League became the only allowed party. The National Assembly was established, which, based on P√§ts' guidelines, legalised an authoritarian form of government in the constitution, with the president as head of state with broad powers. Parliament's rights were curtailed and the Riigikogu became a bicameral body. The Constitution curtailed the democratic rights of the people. The economy began to grow. The kroon was devalued, the state often interfered in the economy. Councils, committees and institutes were set up to account for economic resources; a prospective plan was drawn up for the promotion of certain sectors of the economy. The role of the state in private enterprise was increased and state-owned enterprises were expanded. Greater emphasis was put on advancing Estonian industry. Exports increased, foreign trade balance turned positive (P√§ts conducted realpolitik, trading with western democracies, Hitler's Germany and the USSR). Welfare of the population improved: living standards improved, unemployment disappeared, cost of living fell. The role of the military was increased, conservative and nationalist values were propagated through the Riikliku Propaganda Talitus (National Propaganda Service). As a founding father of the Estonian nation and his actions later on, P√§ts could also be seen as a Caesar figure as like Caesar he moved from a position of power within a democratic framework to establish an authoritarian regime, like Caesar, he centralized authority, bypassing traditional checks and balances, and justified his actions as necessary for stability and the nation. He also sought to solidify his rule through public works, reforms, and the cultivation of a strong personal following, presenting himself as necessary for the nation's survival and stability.

Let us now turn to the very consciousness of their own race among Ukrainians - to Ukrainian racism. This consciousness, which was to some extent lost by the elite of recent decades, began to grow only in the last twenty years [This text was written in 1937]. This consciousness has grown stronger in recent years, perhaps because for centuries there has not been such a clear desire of Ukraine's enemies to destroy the race itself. It is not even a question of physical destruction; the very atmosphere of "projects to destroy" Ukrainians is enough. In this atmosphere, a peculiar sense of solidarity with one's own blood in contrast to outsiders arises. This sense of the vitality and longevity of one's own race, and at the same time the constant threat to the race from the environment, eventually produces a deep sense of solitude in the Ukrainian race. The most obvious thing about Ukrainians is their consciousness of indifference, of the common struggle of all peoples or races against Ukraine, and their desire for destructive action. The greedy terms of "brotherly cooperation" against the background of Slavism, on the basis of Marxism, or in solidarity with Western culture will not cover the absolute lack of help from people and the material world in general. The only power is one's own strength, one's own blood, the bloodline, and this sense of solitude finally stirs up the most secret, deepest, belief in supernatural forces and their care. The struggle to express oneself and to exist in general will give the Ukrainian family a deeper sense of Christianity. ‚Äî Yuriy Lypa @FaithAndBlood

The Modern Soldier How I see standing behind me Injun fighters, Koryos, Crusaders, Hajduks, and Cossack Hetmans, Men of honor who'd shoot traitors and backbiters, I see Conquistadors, Grognards, and a Landsknecht-man. How I wish to march to battle as they once did! Yet where is my Church, liberty, fatherland, and folk? All worth fighting for, our sadist Jew master forbid, Lifetimes suffering under their despotic yoke. So why fight? To fight for the sake of fighting! So why kill? To kill for the sake of killing! So why die? To die for the sake of dying! Killing poor bastards I hate for rich bastards I hate, From Kandahar Province to the Sahara's heat, How I defied death's kiss on our first romantic date, Not so of the hajji scum I stabbed, shot, and beat! I stand pensive, who is my friend, who is my foe? Confusion wrought through my fathers' sacred homeland, And now by staring at their faces I no longer know, Their heroic legacy grounded down into sand... My next adventure, to the Steppe or the Orient, Perhaps in the tropics or to lands travelled well, Corpses of Chechen, Chinaman, or Persian to dissect, War, my only bride with whom forever I'll dwell. Rifles loaded, bayonets fixed, time for the next charge, I stab the bastard, eat his gore and drink his blood, But he stabs me too, I fall from a wound so large, My mind has one thought as I bleed out and drown in mud... "Lord Jesus Christ, Son of God, Have mercy on me, A sinner..."

NS use of the Celtic cross in Vichy France, The National Teams was created in 1942 to involve young volunteers (from 12 to 25 years old, girls and boys) in the protection and relief of populations threatened by war (bombings, etc.). The National Teams do not have a specific uniform, they are distinguished only by the wearing of the armband and badges (Celtic cross). Volunteers are sometimes equipped with an Adrian helmet with a painted Celtic cross and E.N. mention. Analyst Comments: Online, the reaction to Hunter Biden‚Äôs pardon has been mixed. Most people seem to be reflecting on the hypocrisy of Joe Biden pardoning a family member when he explicitly stated that he would not do that, while many others have taken the perspective that Biden‚Äôs act was a respectable one. However, for those equating Biden‚Äôs act as one of a father doing anything to save his son, one detail might derail that wholesome thought. Hunter‚Äôs pardon was a blanket amnesty, covering anything Hunter might have done over a period of 11 years. Considering the potential crimes that he may have committed that we will never even know about (because no investigation will ever be conducted now), this distinction is important and has a wider range of implications than a simple case of corruption. For instance, if we were to find out that Hunter Biden was the kingpin of the Epstein human trafficking network, he‚Äôs already been pardoned for it. Though no one actually expects any member of society‚Äôs elite to actually serve a sentence for a crime they have committed, by issuing a blanket pardon the investigations into other crimes (and any quasi-realistic hope of any sort of truth coming to light) are effectively shut down. This means that there may be substantial crimes (and victims) that we will never even know about in the first place, and untold levels of corruption that cannot be stopped because the American people simply won‚Äôt ever know about it. Wanting Hunter to serve the sentence for crimes that he was convicted of in court is largely irrelevant; framing the issue in terms of hypocrisy and honor is missing out on the larger concerns. Far more concerning are the smaller details of his specific corruption and crimes that he was never even criminally charged with that could have been investigated if a blanket pardon had not been granted. If Hunter was found guilty of something Joe Biden himself was also involved in, such as the Burisma/Ukraine connection, this pardon effectively silences those investigations too. As such, this pardon probably isn‚Äôt really about Hunter at all; after all no one has prosecuted Hunter for the disturbing content found on his laptop. In reality, this is probably more about Joe Biden insulating himself from at least one avenue of prosecution that could not be quelled by the standard power and influence that former Presidents within the Democratic Party usually have. By framing the issue as Joe Biden doing ‚Äúanything to save his son‚Äù is rejecting the other side of the coin‚Ä¶that there are many others that would also do anything to save their sons (and daughters) from the Biden family. Negating this latter idea would also be a disservice to the lives lost in Ukraine, as now that any potential corruption investigation has been shut down, we may never know the full extent of what really happened in Ukraine. In 1951, at 66 years of age, Nils Gustaf H√•kansson participated in the 1,764 km (1,096 mi) race Sverigeloppet from Haparanda to Ystad. The maximum age for contestants was 40 years, but, nevertheless, H√•kansson participated informally, starting one minute after the last of them had set off and wearing a shirt on which he had written a big zero as his race number. The race was run in stages, and while the others slept, H√•kansson would pedal up to three days without sleeping. During the contest, he was presented as "St√•lfarfar" or "Steel Grandpa," and many newspapers covered his story, making him famous as the nation followed his journey through the country. After 6 days, 14 hours and 20 minutes, he arrived in Ystad - 24 hours before the contestants. There was a parade with a marching band, fire brigades and H√•kansson seated on the shoulders of younger men. The next day he had an audience with King Gustaf VI Adolf of Sweden.

The quietest charge controller in terms of RF that I am aware of and use is the Morningstar TS-45/60 that can be set to be a simple on/off charge controller that eliminates noise from PWM charging. MPPT charge controllers are the nosiest in terms of undesirable RF that can also interfere with HF transceivers. Charge controllers can be located several feet underground inside a fallout shelter and/or inside metal containers that act like a Faraday cage in reverse, and wiring to the outside can be housed in metal EMT piping to reduce RF emitted by a PV system.

cleaned_message: Lethally poor? No problem. Buy cheap ACU or UCP, digital tiger camo and dye it. Here is a crash course. Wash all your gear. Dawn duck soap, scrub brush. Get to work. Scrub the entire pouch and gear all over to loosen dirt and debris. Rinse. Fill bin with enough super hot water to cover the gear. Toss in dye. Mix. Stir constantly. Monitor how worn pouches look and pull them early. Newer and better condition pieces take longer. Pull and compare regularly. If the dye isn't taking, add some vinegar and keep stirring. The more materials you dye, you need more dye. Be careful not to overdye. Overdye will make one or more colors of a pattern disappear. Pull the items let drain, do not rinse. Hang dry. Once completely dry, rinse in a bin, dry again or wash. Your items should be ready to use after dried. Every piece and material takes different. Monitor the pieces often and pull. Once the item is dried completely it's very hard to remove the color. When wet it is much easier. So let it dry.

DIME DRILLS Four fundamentals of good shooting are: 1. Body positioning 2. Breathing 3. Sight Picture/Sight Alignment 4. Trigger Squeeze You can practice all 4 of these from the comfort of your home by doing Dime Drills. All you will need is your weapon, a dime and a target to sight in on. To do a dime drill: 1. Take the mag out and ensure your weapon is cleared. 2. Assume the position. 3. Charge your weapon. 4. Place a dime on the muzzle device or barrel. 5. Sight in and squeeze the trigger without causing the dime to fall off. 6. Repeat Do more to do more gooder

Key takeaway, you must be ready to exploit your situation or any victory you achieve is pointless. Once you have the initiative you must maintain it, or your opponent will seize it from you. The draft, which was in effect from 1940 to 1975, was to fill slots that were not filled by regular recruiting. The amount at any given time needed depended on how many volunteers would show up. You would get a draft notice with a date and location to appear. All your affairs had to be in order as if you could not provide an adequate reason for deferment you leave directly for basic training. Men would lose jobs, houses, cars, etc, as they wouldn't be able to make payments with that new E-1 private salary. This is a major issue that would have to be addressed that I have not heard brought up by anyone pushing for the draft. I would assume that this process would happen at MEPS (military entrance and processing station). MEPS's purpose is, in part, to turn away potential recruits. ASVAB, physical fitness, medical suitability, and legal issues are all things that they screen for. The majority of the population at risk of receiving a draft notice would be turned away at this stage. We live in an incredibly unhealthy society and the system, if it even acknowledges this will certainly not move to solve that problem. The whole MEPS process takes a couple of days. They put you up in a hotel in whatever town you happen to be in, and you can just walk out. Outside of every base, they will have to implement an active military police patrol again, restrict off-base liberty, and not allow civilian attire, and require servicemen to carry leave papers on them at all times like in the old days. Additionally, anyone who has been an NCO in the past decade knows that the way the Army handles hazing charges any drafted private could jam up a command by crying hazing, and with the internet you best believe dudes will be sharing the best ways to juke the system with a quickness. To reinstate the draft would require a reorientation of the military and society at large to implement. Tldr you're not getting drafted because doing so would break the Army.

The American Corsair fleet is one of those lesser known parts of the Second World War. Civilian volunteers working with the Coast Guard, they would patrol the eastern seaboard for German U-boats. Working as a counter to the German's Operation Drumbeat, the unrestricted submarine warfare campaign against the US they would patrol to identify and harass the Germans in order to assist the Coast Guard and Navy anti submarine operations. From January 1942 to June of the same year, some 125 American and other nations merchant ships were sunk by the Germans to a loss of 16 U-boats. After June of 1942, the U-boats began focusing on the operations in the mid Atlantic as it became too dangerous to work so close to the US coast.

While the tools have evolved, the fundamentals of fire & manuver as employed by fighting men has remained largely unchanged for some time. This is a report on the use of infantry equipment by the US Army durning the Korean conflict. Written in plain language and taken directly from the fighting men you can see how they used their tools in practice as opposed to what the written doctrine prescribed. Some interesting insights can be found within it. One point I found interesting was how some soldiers believed that there should be less formal bayonet training, not because they belived it wasn't practical but because they felt that it was better to learn on the job and formal instruction would cause hesitation. I disagree on that specific point, but it's an interesting point that can create a discussion.

Army MEDCOM is set to lose 11.3% of its doctors/providers over the next calendar year. MEDCOM currently has a total of 4,263 doctors/providers which comprise the makeup of General Practitioners, Specialists, Dentists, Veterinarians as well as Physician Assistants (though they‚Äôre not doctors). 9.5% have approved retirement packets, and another 1.8% have tentative retirement/REFRAD/UQR packets working through the system. The rank and numbers are as follows: 246 Colonels - 85 retiring, 22 tentative 480 Lt. Colonels - 72 retiring, 19 tentative 944 Majors - 232 retiring, 29 tentative 1865 Captains - 15 retiring, 8 tentative These numbers portray a significant loss to a critical component of the military. This is why the military has been paying such high retention and incentive bonuses to those in the medical field. These numbers also aren‚Äôt being talked about anywhere else that I‚Äôve seen. The loss of doctors and medical professionals has already been felt by families for years now as appointments for routine exams get pushed back months, and specialty care takes even longer for an appointment. The hardship imposed on service members and their families will likely continue to get worse as a tenth of the provider community is set to leave over the next several months.

This might ruffle some feathers but the truth is that irregural warfare is romanticised and their accomplishments most often over exaggerated. The causality ratio and numbers of dead for the irregulars is always extremely high. They might win a few first engagements due to element of surprise but once that is gone and the larger conventional enemy adapts, improves and overcomes the irregular force shall suffer even more. If we in the west can barely have a cohesive opinion about the war in Ukraine, that is now 2 years old, what is there to realistically dream about minutemen/partisans fighting off a large conventional force? For a irregural groups survival criminal actions and acts of terror will become the norm. If the population looses faith in your cause and starts to blame you for their suffering then you won‚Äôt make it long. It‚Äôs only a matter of time that normal people will tire from all the reprisals, shakedowns, potential harms and unsafe upbringing for kids in a conflict area. We haven‚Äôt even talked about salary and benefits of the fighters and their families. Folks won‚Äôt fight for long if you can‚Äôt provide basic upkeep necessities. ‚ÄúBuT thE TaLibAn!?!?‚Äù Are you ready for 20 years of conflict, involved in illegal trafficking/smuggling, be religiously extreme and loose the majority of engagements? The Taliban received heavy support from local tribes, foreign governments and where extremists. The Taliban won politicly in the long run but lost militarily. Afghanistan is not a Western society with western norms and morals. There are so many cases of failed irregulars that no one mentions them‚Ä¶ rarely do I see posts about it compared to the over glorified few success stories. And those success stories often forget that the irregulars often developed/evolved/merged out of it to actually succeed. By becoming something structural and bigger. We saw what happened during the ‚Äúpandemic‚Äù and how normal average folks reacted to it. Unless you are in a ‚Äútribal‚Äù, strong religious or ideological society with clear ethnical identities many of the irregular forces success factors start to disappear in the grand scale of things. Especially when you can‚Äôt establish a clear political/relations center that draws in foreign or local support. I am all for the knowledge and art of the irregular forces. It isn‚Äôt hopeless but it isn‚Äôt a cake walk that dosen dudes can realistically accomplish without becoming a criminal organisation. Instead I would love to see this: Talk to your neighbours, be involved in local efforts, participate in volunteer aid/reliefs and be a team player to your community or region. A squad of friends dreaming about being partisans is unrealistic, unless you join an already established organisation. But a squad of friends can help to saves lives and provide an area with realistic emergency aid efforts.

url_title: Why This Prototype Combat Rig Could Help Army Soldiers Fight A Possible War With China | Loadout
url_description: A United States Army officer shares a modified combat rig that could offer service members a more optimized alternative to the traditional TAPS, or tactical assault panel system. In November, we spoke with 1st Lt. Zachary Calderone of the 25th Infantry Division during the Army's Joint Pacific Multinational Readiness Center, or JPMRC, training exercise in Hawaii. JPMRC is a large-scale 10-day training exercise where the US Army, along with international partners, utilizes realistic combat scenarios that prepare soldiers for battle with peer adversaries like China. Based in Oahu, the 25th Infantry Division typically trains for combat in jungle environments. On this day, Calderone's platoon was operating in the P'hakuloa Training Area on the island of Hawai'i. While the tactical assault panel system is one of the Army's standard combat rigs, Calderone was tasked by his unit to test out a prototype optimized for jungle warfare. Calderone breaks down the differences between what he calls the "jungle rig" and the standard TAPS rig, pointing out how the new rig offers superior adjustability and breathability. url_description: As the foundational edifice our forefathers built degrades and collapses all around us, it's never been more important to both learn to discern the dark from the light, and to *find your tribe*.. to reject this powerless and passive victim mentality, as if we have no options or agency, and find ways to help create or support parallel structure - parallel culture (art, music, entertainment, literature, philosophy and ideology), parallel groups and clubs, institutions and businesses and communities.. ultimately, parallel ways of living. url_title: Tactics of Physical Pen Testers
url_description: This presentation will highlight some of the most exciting and shocking methods by which my team and I routinely let ourselves in on physical jobs. Many organizations are accustomed to being scared at the results of their network scans and digital penetration tests, but seldom do these tests yield outright "surprise" across an entire enterprise. Some servers are unpatched, some software is vulnerable, and networks are often not properly segmented. No huge shocks there. As head of a Physical Penetration team, however, my deliverable day tends to be quite different. With faces agog, executives routinely watch me describe (or show video) of their doors and cabinets popping open in seconds. Presenter: Deviant Ollam - https://enterthecore.net/ Event: Wild West Hackin' Fest 2017 Special thanks to Wild West Hackin' Fest for letting us share their talks.

cleaned_message: While the tools have evolved, the fundamentals of fire & maneuver as employed by fighting men has remained largely unchanged for some time. This is a report on the use of infantry equipment by the US Army during the Korean conflict. Written in plain language and taken directly from the fighting men you can see how they used there tools in practice as opposed to what the written doctrine prescribed. Some interesting insights can be found within it. One point I found interesting was how some soldiers believed that there should be less formal bayonet training, not because they believed it wasn't practical but because they felt that it was better to learn on the job and formal instruction would cause hesitation. I disagree on that specific point, but it's an interesting point that can create a discussion.
document_filename: Use of Infantry Weapons and Equipment in Korea 1952.pdf

The 1st Alaska Combat Intelligence Platoon, also known as Castner's Cutthroats were one of the more unique units of the American military of it's day but fulfilled a role that is as old as warfighting on the North American continent, that of the scout. Participating in the Aleutian Islands campaign, these hunters, trappers, miners & mountain men would conduct reconnaissance, build improvised landing strips and act as guides & messengers enabling the 7th Infantry Division to focus on its task of reclaiming the territory taken by the Empire of Japan. From Roger's Rangers to Castner's Cutthroats, the scout has been integral to warfighting on the American continent from the beginning.

You know whats awesome? SABOT rounds. You know whats even better? SABOT rounds for your rifle. Known as accelerator rounds, you too can enjoy the high velocity action of tank main guns & M2 machine guns (SLAP rounds are legit check'em out) in your own blaster. For example, you can seat a 5.56 projectile inside of a SABOT cup and load that into a .30 caliber cartridge, giving you an absurd velocity & some great effects on target. There are some special considerations like you cannot use a suppressor or muzzle device due to the SABOT cup separation once the projectile leaves the barrel (I might be wrong on that but thats how main gun SABOTs work and I'm not risking obstructing the muzzle), or that due to the nature of SABOTs there will not be any rifling pattern on the projectile. It's a very interesting tool for the toolbox and something worth looking into if your looking for some cool gat stuff.

Or I guess it is a uniform hieroglyphic, And it means, Sprouting alike in broad zones and narrow zones, Growing among black folks as among white, Kanuck, Tuckahoe, Congressman, Cuff, I give them the same, I receive them the same. And now it seems to me the beautiful uncut hair of graves. Tenderly will I use you curling grass, It may be you transpire from the breasts of young men, It may be if I had known them I would have loved them, It may be you are from old people, or from offspring taken soon out of their mothers‚Äô laps, And here you are the mothers‚Äô laps. This grass is very dark to be from the white heads of old mothers, Darker than the colorless beards of old men, Dark to come from under the faint red roofs of mouths. O I perceive after all so many uttering tongues, And I perceive they do not come from the roofs of mouths for nothing. I wish I could translate the hints about the dead young men and women, And the hints about old men and mothers, and the offspring taken soon out of their laps. What do you think has become of the young and old men? And what do you think has become of the women and children? They are alive and well somewhere, The smallest sprout shows there is really no death, And if ever there was it led forward life, and does not wait at the end to arrest it, And ceas‚Äôd the moment life appear‚Äôd. All goes onward and outward, nothing collapses, And to die is different from what any one supposed, and luckier."

THE POET IN NATURE By Walt Whitman "I walk solitary, unattended, An interval passing at vacancy with nature, acceptive and at ease, Sane, random, negligent hours, Wandering the negligent paths, Withdrawn to muse and meditate in some deep recess. Every day, seclusion‚Äîthe soothing silence, far from the clank of crowds, Every day at least two or three hours of freedom, no talk, no bonds, no dress, no manners, Away from books‚Äîaway from art‚Äîthe lesson learn‚Äôd, pass‚Äôd o‚Äôer, No longer abash‚Äôd, for I can respond as I would not dare elsewhere. Nature is naked, and I am also, Sweet, sane, still nakedness in nature! Ah if poor, sick, prurient humanity might really know you once more! Is not nakedness then indecent? No, not inherently; are we not all naked under our clothes? It is the beholder‚Äôs own thought, inference, distorted construction that is indecent‚Äî It is your thought, your sophistication, your fear, your respectability. Your stale modesties are filthy to such a man as I, There come moods when these clothes of ours are not only too irksome to wear, but are themselves indecent. The inner never-lost rapport we hold with earth, light, air, trees, etc., is not to be realized through eyes and mind only, but through the whole corporeal body. Perhaps indeed he or she to whom the free exhilarating extasy of nakedness in nature has never been eligible (and how many thousands there are!) has not really known what purity is‚Äînor what faith or art or health really is. Nothing can exceed the quiet splendor and freshness, the fresh scent, the peace, the naturalness all around me, I feel the sky, the prairies vast, I feel the ocean and the forest‚Äîsomehow I feel the globe itself swift-swimming in space, Never before did I get so close to nature; never before did she come so close to me. Amid this wild, free scene, how healthy, how joyous, how clean and vigorous and sweet! It seems indeed as if peace and nutriment from heaven subtly filter into me here, How it all nourishes, lulls me, in the way most needed. The disturb‚Äôd passions and the feverish conflict subsided, I stand or sit, musing, my sane or sick spirit here as near at peace as it can be. My spirit at peace, I smile, All is peace here, I am satisfied..."

Ode on the Spring By Thomas Gray "Lo! where the rosy-bosom'd Hours, Fair Venus' train appear, Disclose the long-expecting flowers, And wake the purple year! The Attic warbler pours her throat, Responsive to the cuckoo's note, The untaught harmony of spring: While whisp'ring pleasure as they fly, Cool zephyrs thro' the clear blue sky Their gather'd fragrance fling. Where'er the oak's thick branches stretch A broader, browner shade; Where'er the rude and moss-grown beech O'er-canopies the glade, Beside some water's rushy brink With me the Muse shall sit, and think (At ease reclin'd in rustic state) How vain the ardour of the crowd, How low, how little are the proud, How indigent the great! Still is the toiling hand of Care: The panting herds repose: Yet hark, how thro' the peopled air The busy murmur glows! The insect youth are on the wing, Eager to taste the honied spring, And float amid the liquid noon: Some lightly o'er the current skim, Some show their gaily-gilded trim Quick-glancing to the sun. To Contemplation's sober eye Such is the race of man: And they that creep, and they that fly, Shall end where they began. Alike the busy and the gay But flutter thro' life's little day, In fortune's varying colours drest: Brush'd by the hand of rough Mischance, Or chill'd by age, their airy dance They leave, in dust to rest. Methinks I hear in accents low The sportive kind reply: Poor moralist! and what art thou? A solitary fly! Thy joys no glitt'ring female meets, No hive hast thou of hoarded sweets, No painted plumage to display: On hasty wings thy youth is flown; Thy sun is set, thy spring is gone‚Äî We frolic, while 'tis May."

Through primrose tufts, in that green bower, The periwinkle trailed its wreaths; And ‚Äôtis my faith that every flower Enjoys the air it breathes. The birds around me hopped and played, Their thoughts I cannot measure:‚Äî But the least motion which they made It seemed a thrill of pleasure. The budding twigs spread out their fan, To catch the breezy air; And I must think, do all I can, That there was pleasure there. If this belief from heaven be sent, If such be Nature‚Äôs holy plan, Have I not reason to lament What man has made of man?"

II As thus the patient Dam assiduous sits, Not to be tempted from her tender Task, Or by sharp Hunger, or by smooth Delight, Tho the whole loosen‚Äôd Spring around Her blows, Her sympathizing Lover takes his Stand High on th‚Äô opponent Bank, and ceaseless sings The tedious Time away; or else supplies Her place a moment, while she sudden flits To pick the scanty Meal. Th‚Äô appointed Time With pious Toil fulfill‚Äôd, the callow Young, Warm‚Äôd and expanded into perfect Life, Their brittle Bondage break, and come to Light, A helpless Family, demanding Food With constant Clamour. O what Passions then, What melting Sentiments of kindly Care, On the new Parents seize! Away they fly Affectionate, and undesiring bear The most delicious Morsel to their Young, Which equally distributed, again The Search begins. Even so a gentle Pair, By Fortune sunk, but form‚Äôd of generous Mold, And charm‚Äôd with Cares beyond the vulgar Breast, In some lone Cott amid the distant Woods, Sustain‚Äôd alone by providential Heaven, Oft, as they weeping eye their infant Train, Check their own Appetites and give them all. Nor Toil alone they scorn: exalting Love, By the great Father of the Spring inspir‚Äôd, Gives instant Courage to the fearful Race, And to the simple Art. With stealthy Wing, Should some rude Foot their woody Haunts molest, Amid a neighbouring Bush they silent drop, And whirring thence, as if alarm‚Äôd, deceive Th‚Äô unfeeling School-Boy. Hence, around the Head Of wandering Swain, the white-wing‚Äôd Plover wheels Her sounding Flight, and then directly on In long Excursion skims the level Lawn, To tempt him from her Nest. The Wild-Duck, hence, O‚Äôer the rough Moss, and o‚Äôer the trackless Waste The Heath-Hen flutters, (pious Fraud!) to lead The hot pursuing Spaniel far astray. Be not the Muse asham‚Äôd, here to bemoan Her Brothers of the Grove, by tyrant Man Inhuman caught, and in the narrow Cage From Liberty confin‚Äôd, and boundless Air. Dull are the pretty Slaves, their Plumage dull, Ragged, and all its brightening Lustre lost; Nor is that sprightly Wildness in their Notes, Which, clear and vigorous, warbles from the Beech. Oh then, ye Friends of Love and Love-taught Song, Spare the soft Tribes, this barbarous Art forbear! If on your Bosom Innocence can win, Music engage, or Piety persuade. But let not chief the Nightingale lament Her ruin‚Äôd Care, too delicately fram‚Äôd To brook the harsh Confinement of the Cage. Oft when, returning with her loaded Bill, Th‚Äô astonish‚Äôd Mother finds a vacant Nest, By the hard Hand of unrelenting Clowns Robb‚Äôd, to the Ground the vain Provision falls; Her Pinions ruffle, and low-drooping scarce Can bear the Mourner to the poplar Shade; Where, all abandon‚Äôd to Despair, she sings Her Sorrows thro the Night; and, on the Bough, Sole-sitting, still at every dying Fall Takes up again her lamentable Strain Of winding Woe; till wide around the Woods Sigh to her Song, and with her Wail resound. But now the feather‚Äôd Youth their former Bounds, Ardent, disdain; and, weighing oft their Wings, Demand the free Possession of the Sky. This one glad Office more, and then dissolves Parental Love at once, now needless grown. Unlavish Wisdom never works in vain. ‚ÄôTis on some Evening, sunny, grateful, mild, When nought but Balm is breathing thro the Woods, With yellow Lustre bright, that the new Tribes Visit the spacious Heavens, and look abroad On Nature‚Äôs Common, far as they can see, Or wing, their Range, and Pasture. O‚Äôer the Boughs Dancing about, still at the giddy Verge Their Resolution fails; their Pinions till, In loose Libration stretch‚Äôd, to trust the Void Trembling refuse: till down before them fly The Parent-Guides, and chide, exhort, command, Or push them off. The surging Air receives The Plumy Burden; and their self-taught Wings Winnow the waving Element. On Ground Alighted, bolder up again they lead, Farther and farther on, the lengthening Flight; Till vanish‚Äôd every Fear, and every Power Rouz‚Äôd into Life and Action, light in Air Th‚Äô acquitted Parents see their soaring Race, And once rejoicing never know them more."

The Seasons: Spring By James Thomson I "As rising from the vegetable World My Theme ascends, with equal Wing ascend, My panting Muse; and hark, how loud the Woods Invite you forth in all your gayest Trim. Lend me your Song, ye Nightingales! oh pour The mazy-running Soul of Melody Into my varied Verse! while I deduce, From the first Note the hollow Cuckoo sings, The Symphony of Spring, and touch a Theme Unknown to Fame, the Passion of the Groves. When first the Soul of Love is sent abroad, Warm thro the vital Air, and on the Heart Harmonious seizes, the gay Troops begin, In gallant Thought, to plume the painted Wing; And try again the long-forgotten Strain, At first faint-warbled. But no sooner grows The soft Infusion prevalent, and wide, Than, all alive, at once their Joy o‚Äôerflows In Musick unconfin‚Äôd. Up-springs the Lark, Shrill-voic‚Äôd, and loud, the Messenger of Morn; Ere yet the Shadows fly, he mounted sings Amid the dawning Clouds, and from their Haunts Calls up the tuneful Nations. Every Copse Deep-tangled, Tree irregular, and Bush Bending with dewy Moisture, o‚Äôer the Heads Of the coy Quiristers that lodge within, Are prodigal of harmony. The Thrush And Wood-lark, o‚Äôer the kind contending Throng Superior heard, run thro‚Äô the sweetest Length Of Notes; when listening Philomela deigns To let them joy, and purposes, in Thought Elate, to make her Night excel their Day. The Black-bird whistles from the thorny Brake; The mellow Bullfinch answers from the Grove: Nor are the Linnets, o‚Äôer the flow‚Äôring Furze Pour‚Äôd out profusely, silent. Join‚Äôd to these Innumerous Songsters, in the freshening Shade Of new-sprung Leaves, their Modulations mix Mellifluous. The Jay, the Rook, the Daw, And each harsh Pipe discordant heard alone, Aid the full Concert: while the Stock-dove breathes A melancholy Murmur thro‚Äô the whole. ‚ÄôTis Love creates their Melody, and all This Waste of Music is the Voice of Love; That even to Birds, and Beasts, the tender Arts Of pleasing teaches. Hence the glossy kind Try every winning way inventive Love Can dictate, and in Courtship to their Mates Pour forth their little Souls. First, wide around, With distant Awe, in airy Rings they rove, Endeavouring by a thousand Tricks to catch The cunning, conscious, half-averted Glance Of their regardless Charmer. Should she seem Softening the least Approvance to bestow, Their Colours burnish, and by Hope inspir‚Äôd, They brisk advance; then, on a sudden struck, Retire disorder‚Äôd; then again approach; In fond rotation spread the spotted Wing, And shiver every Feather with Desire. Connubial Leagues agreed, to the deep Woods They haste away, all as their Fancy leads, Pleasure, or Food, or secret Safety prompts; That Nature‚Äôs great Command may be obey‚Äôd, Nor all the sweet Sensations they perceive Indulg‚Äôd in vain. Some to the Holly-Hedge Nestling repair, and to the Thicket some; Some to the rude Protection of the Thorn Commit their feeble Offspring. The cleft Tree Offers its kind Concealment to a Few, Their Food its Insects, and its Moss their Nests. Others apart far in the grassy Dale, Or roughening Waste, their humble Texture weave. But most in woodland Solitudes delight, In unfrequented Glooms, or shaggy Banks, Steep, and divided by a babbling Brook, Whose Murmurs soothe them all the live-long Day, When by kind Duty fix‚Äôd. Among the Roots Of Hazel, pendant o‚Äôer the plaintive Stream, They frame the first Foundation of their Domes; Dry Sprigs of Trees, in artful Fabrick laid, And bound with Clay together. Now ‚Äôtis nought But restless Hurry thro the busy Air, Beat by unnumer‚Äôd Wings. The Swallow sweeps The slimy Pool, to build his hanging House Intent. And often, from the careless Back Of Herds and Flocks, a thousand tugging Bills Pluck Hair and Wool; and oft, when unobserv‚Äôd, Steal from the Barn a Straw: till soft and warm, Clean, and compleat, their Habitation grows.

A very hunter did I rush Upon the prey:‚Äîwith leaps and springs I follow'd on from brake to bush; But She, God love her! feared to brush The dust from off its wings."

A Bird, came down the Walk By Emily Dickinson "A Bird, came down the Walk - He did not know I saw - He bit an Angle Worm in halves And ate the fellow, raw, And then, he drank a Dew From a convenient Grass - And then hopped sidewise to the Wall To let a Beetle pass - He glanced with rapid eyes, That hurried all abroad - They looked like frightened Beads, I thought, He stirred his Velvet Head. - Like one in danger, Cautious, I offered him a Crumb, And he unrolled his feathers, And rowed him softer Home - Than Oars divide the Ocean, Too silver for a seam, Or Butterflies, off Banks of Noon, Leap, plashless as they swim."

THE FOREST REVERIE by Edgar Allan Poe "‚ÄôTis said that when The hands of men Tamed this primeval wood, And hoary trees with groans of wo, Like warriors by an unknown foe, Were in their strength subdued, The virgin Earth Gave instant birth To springs that ne‚Äôer did flow That in the sun Did rivulets run, And all around rare flowers did blow The wild rose pale Perfumed the gale, And the queenly lily adown the dale (Whom the sun and the dew And the winds did woo), With the gourd and the grape luxuriant grew. So when in tears The love of years Is wasted like the snow, And the fine fibrils of its life By the rude wrong of instant strife Are broken at a blow Within the heart Do springs upstart Of which it doth now know, And strange, sweet dreams, Like silent streams That from new fountains overflow, With the earlier tide Of rivers glide Deep in the heart whose hope has died Quenching the fires its ashes hide, Its ashes, whence will spring and grow Sweet flowers, ere long, The rare and radiant flowers of song!"

The Snow-Storm By Ralph Waldo Emerson "Announced by all the trumpets of the sky, Arrives the snow, and, driving o'er the fields, Seems nowhere to alight: the whited air Hides hills and woods, the river, and the heaven, And veils the farm-house at the garden's end. The sled and traveller stopped, the courier's feet Delayed, all friends shut out, the housemates sit Around the radiant fireplace, enclosed In a tumultuous privacy of storm. Come see the north wind's masonry. Out of an unseen quarry evermore Furnished with tile, the fierce artificer Curves his white bastions with projected roof Round every windward stake, or tree, or door. Speeding, the myriad-handed, his wild work So fanciful, so savage, nought cares he For number or proportion. Mockingly, On coop or kennel he hangs Parian wreaths; A swan-like form invests the hidden thorn; Fills up the farmer's lane from wall to wall, Maugre the farmer's sighs; and, at the gate, A tapering turret overtops the work. And when his hours are numbered, and the world Is all his own, retiring, as he were not, Leaves, when the sun appears, astonished Art To mimic in slow structures, stone by stone, Built in an age, the mad wind's night-work, The frolic architecture of the snow."

Lo! now the direful monster, whose skin clings To his strong bones, strides o‚Äôer the groaning rocks: He withers all in silence, and in his hand Unclothes the earth, and freezes up frail life. He takes his seat upon the cliffs, the mariner Cries in vain. Poor little wretch! that deal‚Äôst With storms; till heaven smiles, and the monster Is driven yelling to his caves beneath Mount Hecla."

Sonnet 97 By William Shakespeare "How like a winter hath my absence been From thee, the pleasure of the fleeting year! What freezings have I felt, what dark days seen! What old December's bareness everywhere! And yet this time remov'd was summer's time, The teeming autumn, big with rich increase, Bearing the wanton burthen of the prime, Like widow'd wombs after their lords' decease: Yet this abundant issue seem'd to me But hope of orphans and unfather'd fruit; For summer and his pleasures wait on thee, And thou away, the very birds are mute; Or if they sing, 'tis with so dull a cheer That leaves look pale, dreading the winter's near."

Mont Brevent By George Santayana "O dweller in the valley, lift thine eyes To where, above the drift of cloud, the stone Endures in silence, and to God alone Upturns its furrowed visage, and is wise. There yet is being, far from all that dies, And beauty where no mortal maketh moan, Where larger planets swim the liquid zone, And wider spaces stretch to calmer skies. Only a little way above the plain Is snow eternal. Round the mountain's knees Hovers the fury of the wind and rain. Look up, and teach thy noble heart to cease From endless labour. There is perfect peace Only a little way above thy pain."
